### Phase 7 UAT: Role System Refactor & Tech Debt
### Server must be running on localhost:8080

### ===== Test 1: UserRole in login/register API response =====
### Register a new user — response should have "role": "USER" as flat string

POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "uat-phase7@test.com",
  "password": "TestPass123!",
  "firstName": "UAT",
  "lastName": "Tester"
}

### Login with that user — response should have accessToken, refreshToken
### Save the accessToken for subsequent requests

POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ignis.fatue@gmail.com",
  "password": "Mm.12345"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.accessToken);
    client.global.set("refreshToken", response.body.refreshToken);
%}

### ===== Test 2: Admin route protection with typed UserRole =====
### GET user by ID as non-admin — should return 403 Forbidden

GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### ===== Test 4: Verify user has role_id (via GET /me) =====
### GET own profile — response should include "role": "USER"

GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### ===== Test 7: JWT encodes role as flat string =====
### Decode the accessToken at jwt.io or inspect the login response above.
### The JWT payload should contain a "role" claim with value "USER" (flat string).
### (Use the accessToken from the login response above)

### ===== Cleanup: Logout =====

POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
